"```sql\nSELECT b.category, SUM(b.amount) AS total_amount\nFROM event e\nJOIN budget b ON e.event_id = b.link_to_event\nWHERE e.event_name = 'April Speaker'\nGROUP BY b.category\nORDER BY total_amount ASC;\n```\n\nThis SQL query joins the `event` and `budget` tables to find the total amount budgeted for each category of the 'April Speaker' event. It groups the results by category and orders them in ascending order based on the total amount budgeted."